Here’s my new drawing of Scarlett Johansson - this one has been in the to-draw folder for some time but I knew it would be tricky because of the subtle value variations but I was up for a challenge & decided to give it a go. I actually used it for a tutorial on patreon too - where I spend time explaining the importance of a light touch when rendering subtle value changes.

I did this drawing in graphite & a touch of white gel + conte on cream paper. Its 11” x 14”
